Construction of the East Campus of Rich Township High School, financed by a $1,600,000 bond issue, began in September, 1952.
In 1955, a $450,000 bond issue financed the addition of 12 classrooms and a gymnasium.
In 1966, a $2,700,000 bond issue was authorized by voters in the district. $2,500,000 of the bond issue was for the purpose of building and equipping additions to the Central and East Campus facilities.
